{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":16022,"record_hash":"sha256:c35097f2a806d528197bf8151221113a926164b9ac4f094177318521657d013c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:35:33.684Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: b8d6c0\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2858\nOutput:\n# Architecture\n\n## Crate Boundary\n\n`crates/but-agentlog` owns agent log capture and GitMeta writes.\n\nIt should not depend on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`,\n`but-cursor`, workspace rules, or legacy virtual-branch APIs. The POC should use\na closed `Agent` enum and explicit Codex/Claude parser branches, not a plugin\nframework.\n\n## POC Boundary\n\nFor the first implementation:\n\n- support Codex and Claude only\n- require explicit `--transcript-path`\n- default to the `project` GitMeta target\n- write redacted, shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys\n- do not discover sessions\n- do not infer branch, change, commit, or pull request ownership\n- do not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta\n\nIf this file conflicts with [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md),\nthe implementation contract wins.\n\n## CLI Integration\n\nThe `but` crate should expose only the hidden top-level hook:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture ...\n```\n\nThe command shape and argument mapping live in `but-agentlog`. The `but` crate\nshould remain limited to feature-gating, output mode selection, and delegation.\n\nWithout the `agentlog` feature, the command is not compiled or recognized. With\nthe feature enabled, it is callable but hidden from help.\n\n## Module Ownership\n\nKeep ownership narrow:\n\n- `cli.rs`: hidden command type and CLI-to-capture mapping\n- `capture.rs`: orchestration and repository-safe source identity\n- `transcript.rs`: Codex/Claude JSONL parsing and normalized record extraction\n- `gitmeta.rs`: GitMeta target/key/value writes and transcript envelope storage\n- `redaction.rs`: string/value redaction only\n\nAvoid adding abstractions unless a second concrete use in the POC needs them.\n\n## Capture Pipeline\n\n```text\nCLI command\n  -> resolve repository and explicit transcript path\n  -> parse transcript snapshot\n  -> derive durable session/source keys\n  -> write GitMeta session metadata, record hashes, and transcript en\n[TRUNCATED]\ntcher, broad machine scan, or remote exchange\n- GitMeta serialization, fetch, sync, and push integration remain future work\n\nThe data shape is intentionally pointed at two later product flows:\n\n- handoff, where a session captured on one machine can later be read from GitMeta\n  and resumed on another machine or by another agent\n- review sharing, where a branch or pull request can later reference one or more\n  project sessions for a GitButler web timeline\n\nThose flows are why the POC uses durable project sessions plus future\nrelationship keys, rather than storing transcript data directly on a branch or\ninside `meta:local:*`.\n\nA good first command shape is:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture \\\n  --agent codex \\\n  --transcript-path <path> \\\n  --target project\n```\n\n## Design Bias\n\nPrefer safety and auditability over clever discovery. It is better for the POC\nto capture nothing unless given an exact transcript than to accidentally capture\nthe wrong or private session.\n\n## Documents\n\n- [Spec Iteration Process](spec-iteration-process.md)\n- [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md)\n- [Requirements and Goals](requirements-and-goals.md)\n- [Architecture](architecture.md)\n- [GitMeta Data Model](gitmeta-data-model.md)\n- [Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md)\n- [Capture Workflow](capture-workflow.md)\n- [Agentlog Maintainability Playbook](maintainability-playbook.md)\n\n## Reference Material\n\n- [GitMeta specification](https://git-meta.com/spec/)\n- [GitMeta targets and keys](https://git-meta.com/spec/